  "abstract": "\u003cjats:p\u003eUsing simulated data from GAW 12, problem 2, we further develop a novel technique to detect and use significant covariates in linkage analysis. The method, first introduced by Rice et al. [Genet Epidemiol 17(Suppl. 1):S691–5, 19991, uses logistic regression to model perturbation in sharing as a function of covariate levels. The original method allows use of all sib pairs (concordant affected, concordant unaffected, and discordant). Here we extend this method to include cousin pairs in analysis. © 2001 Wiley‐Liss, Inc.\u003c/jats:p\u003e",
